# Debug documentation

`DEBUG.md` at the repo root is the **canonical operator guide** for `/debug/*` flows, prerequisites, and owned-catalog/inventory chains.

When your change affects any of the following, **update `DEBUG.md` in the same commit**:

- Debug routes, layout, or page behavior (`src/app/debug/**`)
- Owned catalog, instance APIs, or sync (`/api/catalog/*`, `/api/user/inventory/*`, `/api/bungie/sync`)
- Prerequisites (manifest, OAuth, sync steps) or edge-case tables
- New debug pages or removed routes

Also bump the **Last reviewed** date in `DEBUG.md` when you edit it.

Feature `specs/*/quickstart.md` files stay as scenario checklists; do not duplicate full flow docs there—link to `DEBUG.md` instead when adding cross-cutting prerequisites.
